                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Chargé
                            <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <hi rend="italic">
                            <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-03-30">March 30, 1906</date>
                        </hi>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(In answer to Mr. Wilson’s telegram of March 28, Mr. Root says that obstructions
                    due to military exigencies, while perhaps explaining temporary restrictions of
                    visiting aliens, does not meet the rapidly developing situation of the
                    absorption of a great part of the commercial and mining opportunities of
                    Manchuria by the freely admitted Japanese. Such opportunities are absolutely
                    closed now to aliens, and even the establishment and recovery of rights
                    acquired, before the late war by American citizens and others are so impeded as
                    to occasion loss and injury to the interested parties. The department is
                    informed that in some quarters, as at Newchwang, the military authorities have
                    decreed land registration for effecting valuable transfers with a view to their
                    subsequent validation by China. If this condition continues China may find
                    herself, after the Japanese occupancy has ceased, the merely nominal sovereign
                    of a territory of which the temporary occupants have appropriated the material
                    advantages.)</p>
            </div>
